                video_url: null,
                "description": "The city centre is just a six minute journey from the airport by train, while the streets are perfect for walking on foot. - www.express.co.uk",
                "content": "Geneva is a walkable city for tourists Geneva is a beautiful destination to visit, not just for its stunning scenery and cultural offerings but also for its walkability. While one of the most expensive places to visit in Europe, tourists who love to explore on foot are spoiled for choice in this Switzerland city. What's more, the city centre is just a six minute journey from the airport, making it the perfect destination for people doing short trips who don't want to spend time in a long transfer. According to geneva.info, Geneva airport is located four kilometers from the city. A train journey between the Geneva Airport and central railway station in the city (Gare Cornavin) takes six minutes, while a bus takes about 20 minutes. Tourists can take public transport around the city without spending a penny and can hop on and off its extensive transport network for free. Geneva's city centre... Sophie Law",
